JsonInputServerSocket
public class InputServerSocket
extends StreamSocketServer

Server Socket for Input Stream to Stream Engine. Starts two Netty Servers - ingestionServer, dataSourceServer. IngestionServer - TCP endpoint for users to connect (or DataIngestionRouter clients to connect) to write data for the given input stream (the stream has a fixed StreamSchema). DataSourceServer - TCP endpoint for StreamEngine Process (RTS) process to connect and receive data. RelayChannel - IngestionServer passes on the data it receives (potential after transforming it to GDAT format) to the StreamEngine TCP client via the Relay Channel.
